# License Matrix

This umbrella file declares the per-crate / per-asset license layout.
Authoritative SPDX headers live in each file; this index is a guide.

| Path                       | SPDX                           | Notes                                                          |
|----------------------------|--------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|
| `crates/signal-algebra/`   | `MIT`                          | Source MIT. v0.1 ships as `rlib` only (cdylib in v0.2 with the C ABI). Linked binary inherits GPL-3.0-or-later via L1. |
| `spec/signal-algebra/`     | `Apache-2.0 OR MIT`            | Dual-licensed spec; permits third-party integration.           |
| `crates/c2pa-emit/`        | `MIT`                          | Wraps c2pa-rs (MIT).                                           |
| `bins/kittler-archive/`    | `GPL-3.0-or-later` (v0.2)      | Will link GNU Radio, inherits GPL-3.0. v0.1: absent, see `bins/README.md`. |
| `web-stage/`               | `AGPL-3.0-or-later`            | Wraps Strudel (AGPL-3.0). Isolated process boundary.           |
| `plugins/ai/`              | `Apache-2.0`                   | Sidecar host. Qwen3 model is **user-pulled**, never bundled.   |
| `signal-ingest/`           | `GPL-3.0-or-later`             | Wraps GNU Radio + Greaseweazle.                                |
| `fixtures/`                | `CC0-1.0` or `Public Domain`   | Internet Archive PD + synthetic signals only.                  |
| `docs/`                    | `CC-BY-SA-4.0`                 |                                                                |
| `governance.md`            | `CC-BY-SA-4.0`                 | Ethical contract; see §G6 proxy interview clause.              |

## Why three licenses?

Kittler's media materiality demands honest license disclosure:
- **MIT** for the algebra core (so third-party UI integrations can exist)
- **GPL-3.0** for binaries that link RF/disk-imaging tools (license inheritance honored)
- **AGPL-3.0** for the web-stage (live-coding venue interactions stay open)

## Qwen3 / Tongyi Qianwen isolation (architectural constraint, not legal opinion)

The `plugins/ai/` sidecar **does not bundle** any Qwen3 model weights.
The distributed binary never ships Tongyi-Qianwen-licensed artifacts.
End users opt-in by running `kittler ai pull qwen3-omni` locally — the model
download is governed solely by the user's acceptance of the Tongyi Qianwen
license terms, not by the OSS distribution channel.

This isolates the OSS license matrix from Tongyi's commercial-use clause.
